The USA has thus lost six consecutive times on European soil and has not won a Ryder Cup in Europe since 1993.
Europe won the trophy when the Danish captain Thomas Bjorn team reached 14.5 points that were needed to beat the United States.
The USA champion Phil Mickelson, who fought for most of the tournament, launched his tee shot in the water at the sixteenth hole of par 3 granting the victory to Francesco Molinari.
